<br>
I do however have a fairly basic request.  When you are asking people to leave a zone so that you can do your scripted event, please do so with courtesy and respect for the players you are evicting.  I would think that very few of these events are spur of the moment things, so advance warning would most definitely be appropriate.  It certainly is more difficult to get 50 people organized, grouped, raided, buffed and ready to go for an event, but please recognize that to some of the smaller people, it can also be very difficult to get their six people together and buffed and to the camp spot that is going to help them advance.  Even though you have the right to ask them to leave, understand that it is frustrating from their point of view.  When the request is phrased more along the lines of &quot;Get the bleep out of my zone now, you noob,&quot; the frustration levels willl definitely rise.   <br>
<br>
In the only instance where I personally have encountered the situation, it was handled quite well, with adequate advance notice and information given so that anyone not familiar with the conventions would understand, and so that everyone would have time to prepare to leave the zone.  I have however heard quite the opposite from some of my guildmembers.  <br>
<br>
Just to reiterate, I am not in any way disagreeing with the conventions listed in this thread, only with the manner in which some people have handled it.  <br>
<br>
Thank you for your time.  <br>
<br>
Slissia Sniggisnake<br>
Iksar Prophet<br>
