TMS planned on warning the zone 1 hour before they started the event to give everyone in the zone, ample time to make arrangements for the disruption.<br>
<br>
I think that on all scripted events that require a clearing of a zone or area, this should be required of the guild that plans to do so. No neccesarily an hour, but that is not really too much to ask.<br>
<br>
Because one guild wants to take on a given event for whatever reason, and that event WILL disrupt an entire zone (or even area of a zone), they should be responsible for ample warning.<br>
<br>
To ensure that &quot;camping&quot; of events is avoided, once a guild starts their warning, they have no more than 1.5 hours (or whatever) to actually start the event.<br>
<br>
To further ensure this, another guild CAN come in during a warning, state their intentions, and &quot;hold guild A to it&quot;.<br>
<br>
These times etc. are all arbitrary, but basically it is reasonable to ask a guild that is interfering with an entire zone to give those in the zone the courtesy of some warning. And conversly to ask those in the zone to leave. Various provisions can be made to ensure that TMS doesnt start &quot;calling&quot; ring war at 10 AM when they plan to do it at 8.<br>
<br>
I also dont think that an entire raid force needs to be present in a zone during the entire &quot;warning&quot; time.<br>
<br>
Something of this nature would have resolved the TMS/TL problem long before it started. And may well help other small guilds from being &quot;steamrolled&quot; in that manner. <p>Hutterr Verbruggen<br>
<br>
61 Druid<br>
<br>
Leader of Fallen Shadows<br>
<br>
Proud to stand behind what I say.</p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#00FFFF>- </font><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency>The Rathe Travel Agency Board</a><font color=#00FFFF> - </font><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11>Guild Representatives Forum</a> <font color=#00FFFF> - </font><a href="http://www.jakefitch.com/rta/Calendar.asp">The Rathe Calendar</a><font color=#00FFFF> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.245d<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

